<t>
<field>TRANSACTION.CODE</field>
<desc>
            <p>
                <p>Validation Rules:</p>
            </p>
            <p>Mandatory input.</p>
            <p>A maximum of 3 characters may be entered.</p>
        </desc>
</t>
<t>
<field>SHORT.DESC</field>
<desc>
            <p>This field may be expanded to allow the user to enter the description of the TRANSACTION.CODE in various languages. Each expansion of the field will correspond to a new language as defined in the LANGUAGE table and will indicate to the user the language in which the description is to be entered. </p>
            <p>
                <p>Validation Rules:</p>
            </p>
            <p>1 to 20 type SS (uppercase alpha or numeric, first character must be alpha) characters.  Multi language field  (Mandatory Input)</p>
        </desc>
</t>
<t>
<field>DESCRIPTION</field>
<desc>
            <p>This field can be expanded to allow the User to enter the description of the TRANSACTION.CODE in various languages.  Each expansion of the field will correspond to a new Language as defined in the LANGUAGE Table and will indicate to the user the Language in which the Description must be entered. </p>
            <p>
                <p>Validation Rules:</p>
            </p>
            <p>3-35 type A (alphanumeric) characters. Multilanguage field. Multivalue field. (Mandatory input)</p>
        </desc>
</t>
<t>
<field>LOCAL.REF</field>
<desc>
            <p>Local Reference Field.  Multivalued field. </p>
            <p>
                <p>Validation Rules:</p>
            </p>
            <p>35 Alphanumeric characters.</p>
        </desc>
</t>
<t>
<field>REVERSAL.MARKER</field>
<desc>
            <p>The transaction entries that are reflected in CRF for Debit/Credit movement depends upon the sign of the numeric entry. ie. if the sign of the transaction amount is negative it shown as a Debit movement and if it is positive it is shown as a Credit movement.</p>
            <p>The entry in this field along with in ACCOUNT.PARAMETER provides the facility to treat reversal entries as follows:</p>
            <p>YES - Reversal entries are reflected as the same CRF type and as the same type of movement as the original entry </p>
            <p>NO or  - Reversal entries are reflected as the same CRF type as the original entry but as an opposite movement </p>
